": "/register", "secondary_button_label": "Explore apps", "secondary_button_url": "/apps"}}, {"type": "FaqBlock", "data": {"heading": "Frequently asked questions", "items": [{"question": "Is Titan BOS only for cleaning businesses?", "answer": "The launch focus is cleaning and adjacent service businesses: residential cleaning, commercial cleaning, bond cleans, Airbnb turnovers, construction cleans, pressure cleaning, window cleaning, solar panel cleaning, detailing, pool, garden, and other field-service modes."}, {"question": "What are Service Modes?", "answer": "Service Modes replace generic workflows with niche-specific terminology, lifecycle stages, checklists, training, compliance logic, artefact generators, and AI knowledge packs."}, {"question": "Does Titan force me to use one AI provider?", "answer": "No. Titan follows a BYO-key philosophy. Use your own AI provider, optional local models such as Ollama where supported, or operate without mandatory AI."}, {"question": "Does Titan charge per AI token?", "answer": "Titan is designed around subscription-first pricing and zero token traps. Provider costs remain under your control when you use your own keys."}, {"question": "Is ZeroPay an accounting system?", "answer": "No. ZeroPay is a payment operations layer. It creates sessions, links, QR codes, reminders, and reconciliation assistance on top of your invoice/accounting source of truth."}, {"question": "Can one company run multiple Service Modes?", "answer": "Yes. A workspace can activate multiple Service Modes at once and each job can load the correct workflow, checklist, compliance logic, and artefact pack."}, {"question": "Does Titan own or resell my business data?", "answer": "No. The Zero doctrine is ownership-first: your records, prompts, API keys, integrations, communication channels, and operating logic stay yours."}, {"question": "How is this different from Jobber, ServiceM8, or Housecall Pro?", "answer": "Those tools are broad service-management products. Titan BOS is positioned as an operating system for service execution with nine apps, Service Modes, AI knowledge packs, training, evidence, compliance, and zero-fee-first payment operations."}, {"question": "Can technicians use it onsite?", "answer": "Yes. Titan Go is the field execution surface for checklists, evidence, photos, notes, status updates, signatures, and completion confidence."}, {"question": "Does the system support offline or device-first operation?", "answer": "The product direction is device-first. Field execution should keep teams productive onsite while syncing operational records when connectivity allows."}]}}, {"type": "CtaBlock", "data": {"heading": "Start your Titan system", "body": "Choose your Service Modes, connect your apps, and let Titan run the operating loop.", "button_label": "Create workspace", "button_url": "/register"}}]}, {"slug": "about", "title": "About Titan BOS", "summary": "Why Titan exists and what Zero means.", "meta_title": "About Titan BOS", "meta_description": "Why Titan exists and what Zero means.", "status": "published", "website_content": [{"type": "HeroBlock", "data": {"eyebrow": "About", "headline": "Why Titan exists", "subheadline": "Titan BOS exists because service businesses do not need more disconnected tools. They need an operating system that understands the work.", "primary_button_label": "Create workspace", "primary_button_url": "/register", "secondary_button_label": "Explore apps", "secondary_button_url": "/apps"}}, {"type": "FeatureGridBlock", "data": {"heading": "The belief", "body": "Titan is built around a few simple convictions.", "features": [{"title": "Service work is operationally specific", "description": "A bond clean is not a pressure wash. A solar service is not a domestic recurring visit."}, {"title": "Software should reduce burden", "description": "Every app should remove a category of stress instead of adding admin."}, {"title": "Ownership matters", "description": "Operators should control 